\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The Neume Tool is for entering Solesmes notation. Calliope's neume and accent design follows the \i Liber Usualis\i0  compiled by the Solesmes community in the first few decades of the 20th century.  The Solesmes notation has become the standard notation scheme for all chant.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 In Calliope, a number of basic neume fragments is available for commonly used forms; other forms may be built up from the basic fragments.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 A full range of accent symbols (\i episemae\i0 ) is available, as well as the accidental (\i molle\i0 ).  Molli can be either attached to a neume or  notated as free-standing signatures (see \b Key Signature Tool\b0 ).  \i Episemae\i0 , \i molli\i0 , and ledger lines are placed automatically.   Examples of neumes are:\par
