\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Select a Neume Tool.  Click on a staff to place the neume where the pointer is.  The selection area of a neume is the bounding box of the neume, however, clicks near individual notes are significant when moving notes.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b Neume placement\b0  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 As for any staff object, neumes are automatically placed when the system is adjusted (see \b Adjustment\b0 ).  However, it is possible to move a whole neume or to move the notes within a neume to new pitches.  To move the whole neume, click anywhere within a neume and hold the mouse button down to drag the neume to a desired location.  The neume attaches itself to the nearest staff.   To move the notes within a neume to other pitches, click on the note and Alternate-drag it to a new pitch.  The neume will deform accordingly.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b The Neume Inspector\b0   \par
